Add support for complex codec configuration

Logstash supports 2 types of codec configuration

1. just setting the codec name this will result in using the codecs default settings
2. using a named hash containting the setting values.

The new input template now supports both options, previously only 1. was supported.
Update logstash log config model to reflect codec change
Disable outputing empty line after codec

Fixed Invalid cross-device link error

If the data-dir and /tmp are on different filesystems, the "process"-run
will throw the exception "Invalid cross-device link". This bug was fixed
by using shutil.move().

Fixed errors with non-utf-8 characters in pcap.py

convert_pcap_to_ecs() throws an exception if it reads non-utf-8
characters. This commit adds a error-handler to TextIOWrapper
that replaces non-utf-8 chars with ?
